Movie Info:

The Outlaw Josey Wales is a 1976 American revisionist Western film set during
and after the American Civil War. It was directed by and starred Clint Eastwood
(as the eponymous Josey Wales), with Chief Dan George, Sondra Locke,
Sam Bottoms, and Geraldine Keams.

The film was adapted by Sonia Chernus and Philip Kaufman from Forrest Carter's
1973 novel The Rebel Outlaw: Josey Wales (republished, as shown in the movie's
opening credits, as Gone to Texas). In 1996, the film was selected for 
preservation in the National Film Registry of the Library of Congress
